<h2>Prefetch Behavior</h2>
<p>
    Attribute-based behavior that implements the <a href="/intents/prefetch/">Prefetch Intent</a> by detecting user conditions
    via browser APIs and triggering resource prefetching at the appropriate eagerness level.
    Part of the <a href="/projects/webresources/">Web Resources</a> ecosystem.
</p>
<p>
    Maps abstract intent conditions (<code>limited-data</code>, <code>low-power</code>, <code>slow-connection</code>)
    to concrete browser APIs. Eagerness levels are translated to DOM events that trigger prefetching
    at the optimal moment &mdash; trading off speculation cost against navigation speed.
</p>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Speculation_Rules_API">Speculation Rules API</a></td>
        <td>Chrome 121+</td>
        <td>Aligns eagerness model (conservative/moderate/eager/immediate) with our intent levels; delegates to native prefetch when available</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver">IntersectionObserver</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td><code>withViewportPrefetch</code> observes link visibility with configurable <code>rootMargin</code> to trigger before element is fully in view</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation">NetworkInformation API</a></td>
        <td>Limited (Chromium)</td>
        <td>Suppresses prefetch when <code>saveData</code> is true or <code>effectiveType</code> is <code>'slow-2g'</code>/<code>'2g'</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API">Battery Status API</a></td>
        <td>Limited (Chromium)</td>
        <td>Suppresses viewport-level prefetch when battery &lt; 20% and not charging</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/rel/prefetch">&lt;link rel="prefetch"&gt;</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>For navigation prefetches, injects <code>&lt;link rel="prefetch"&gt;</code> into <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> for browser-native fetching</td>
    </tr>
</table>

